
[1]congruous

   CONGRUOUS, a. [L.]

   1. Suitable; consistent; agreeable to. Light airy music and a solemn or
   mournful occasion are not congruous. Obedience to God is congruous to
   the light of reason.

   2. Rational; fit.

   It is not congruous that God should be always frightening men into an
   acknowledgment of the truth.
